X-SOURCE-ID:gcal_davisbikeclubwww
SUMMARY:Second Saturday Explorer Ride
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260411T130000
DTSTAMP:20260407T172541Z
UID:um3f9rrqc3e43vqnc0mj7nopip@google.com__20260411
SEQUENCE:1
CREATED:20251104T152227Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Here’s a link to the April second Saturday ride: <a href
 ="https://ridewithgps.com/routes/54531276" target="_blank">https://ridewit
 hgps.com/<wbr />routes/54531276</a><u></u><u></u></p><p>The plan is to sta
 rt from Sutter High School at 9:30 a.m.\, bike 39 miles around the Sutter 
 Buttes\, and then\, if you have time\, have a late lunch in the town of Su
 tter at Sutter Cut Pizzeria\, or maybe French Whisk or Taco Time. Because 
 food is only available at the end of the ride\, you should carry snacks.<u
 ></u><u></u></p><p>More details below. Please let me know if you need addi
 tional information.<u></u><u></u></p><p>Thanks\,<u></u><u></u></p><p>-Anne
 <u></u><u></u></p><p>(916) 206-2922<u></u><u></u></p><ul><li>Date: Second 
 Saturday – April 11\, 2026<u></u><u></u></li><li>Start time: <b>9:30</b
 > a.m.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Start location: Town of Sutter: parking lot 
 of the Sutter Union High School at 2665 Acacia Ave\, Sutter\, CA 95982.<u>
 </u><u></u></li><li>Distance: 39 miles\, ~500 feet of climbing<u></u><u></
 u></li><li>Contact: Anne Huber\; <a href="mailto:anneh@dcn.org" target="_
 blank">anneh@dcn.org</a>\; 916-206-2922<u></u><u></u></li><li>Services (Fo
 od\, water\, bathrooms): No food until end of ride\, so bring a snack. Als
 o\, no real bathrooms along the route.<u></u><u></u></li><li>No need to RS
 VP<u></u><u></u></li><li>Rain cancellation or postponement: communicated v
 ia the listserv.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Pace: 14 - 17 mph with regroups. Th
 e speed is meant to be an indicator of speed on flat terrain with no wind.
  People can go faster if they want as long as they are willing to regroup.
  There might be some stopping for scenery.<u></u><u></u></li><li>Route: <
 a href="https://ridewithgps.com/routes/54531276" target="_blank">https://r
 idewithgps.com/<wbr />routes/54531276</a><u></u><u></u></li></ul><p><u></u
 > <u></u></p><ul><li>For general information about the second Saturday ri
 de and bicycling with the Davis Bike Club\, please see: <a href="https://
 davisbikeclub.org/2nd-sat-explorer-ride/" target="_blank">https://davisbik
 eclub.org/2nd-<wbr />sat-explorer-ride/</a><u></u><u></u></li></ul><p>This
  link includes the following: “Cycling has inherent risks. Any cyclist t
 aking part in a DBC ride releases DBC from any liability. Guests are welco
 me to ride with DBC for one ride\; for subsequent rides\, you must be a me
 mber of the Club. By riding with a DBC group ride you acknowledge that you
  have read and understand this. Helmets are required on all rides.”</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260406T150528Z
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
X-SOURCE:Davis Bike Club
END:VEVENT
