X-SOURCE-URLS:{"UC Davis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/copy-of-datalab-office-hours-in-person"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:DataLab Office Hours (in person)
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260428T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260428T140000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_50755967520459
DESCRIPTION:DataLab offers free in person drop-in office hours during whic
 h UC Davis researchers can obtain data science help and advice on working 
 with their data. During these short\, just-in-time sessions we meet with f
 aculty\, students\, postdoctoral scholars\, and staff from all domains acr
 oss the University. Depending on the nature of your question and our avail
 ability\, it may be possible to schedule a longer follow-up consultation a
 fter your office hours visit.\n\nAppointments are not required. Please com
 plete the brief office hours intake form ahead of time to help us connect 
 you with the right expert for your question.\n\nCommon office hours help t
 opics include:\n\nOpen Source Programming (R\, Python\, Julia\, etc.)Repro
 ducible research computing and data scienceResponsible and ethical data sc
 ienceData gathering\, organization\, databases\, and experimental designDa
 ta analysis\, statistics\, and explorationData visualizationMachine learni
 ng and neural networksText mining and natural language processingGeospatia
 l sciencesRemote and high performance computingComputational pedagogy… a
 nd more!Please note that drop-in office hours are not offered during Unive
 rsity holidays\, academic breaks and finals week. Summer schedule varies. 
 DataLab may only be accessed during Shields Library's business hours. Clic
 k here for detailed directions to DataLab.\n\nNote: We are unable to provi
 de support for assigned coursework (homework assignments\, class projects\
 , etc.) during office hours. If you need such help please contact your ins
 tructor or TA for assistance. If you need help with technical problems suc
 h system administration and hardware issues\, check out the the UC Davis S
 erviceHub and/or contact your departmental IT.
LOCATION:Shields Library\, 360
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/copy-of-datalab-office-hours-
 in-person
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
