BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"UC Davis Library": "https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/tracking-research-impact"}
X-SOURCE-ID:ucdavis_library
SUMMARY:From Idea to Impact: Publishing Your Work — Researcher IDs & Tra
 cking Your Research Impact
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260521T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260521T140000
UID:tag:localist.com\,2008:EventInstance_52332294855434
DESCRIPTION:Build your digital research identity and ensure your work gets
  the credit it deserves with this focused workshop on persistent identifie
 rs and impact tracking. This session provides a practical roadmap for mana
 ging ORCID\, Scopus ID\, and Web of Science profiles to eliminate author a
 mbiguity.\n \n\nWe will also demonstrate how to strategically monitor your
  publication impact using tools like Scopus and Google Scholar\, moving be
 yond simple citation counts to understand your global reach and field-weig
 hted influence.\n \n\nNo previous experience is required. All disciplines 
 are welcome.\n\n\nPlease register for the Zoom link.\n\nThis six-workshop 
 series is a collaboration between the library's Scholarly Communications P
 rogram\, the Researcher Services department\, and Blaisdell Medical Librar
 y. For any questions\, please contact the Scholarly Communication Officer 
 Michael Ladisch (mladisch@ucdavis.edu). Check our events calendar for more
  publishing workshops.
URL:https://events.library.ucdavis.edu/event/tracking-research-impact
X-SOURCE:UC Davis Library
END:VEVENT
